This paper discusses a data management system that enhances data protection by leveraging training set minimization methods, specifically count featurization, in big data applications. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories in computer science, including database systems (cs.DB), computer security and cryptography (cs.CR), machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Therefore, these are the five most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper, ordered from most to least likely.
